Anonymous access lineage
-------------------------
suzume reaches X (Twitter) on an anonymous plane. The guest token activation,
the transaction id signing scheme, and the syndication fallback approach descend
from a lineage of prior free software:

  nitter (AGPL-3.0)  ->  x-cli (AGPL-3.0)  ->  suzume (AGPL-3.0)

Because that lineage is copyleft, suzume is licensed under AGPL-3.0-only. If you
run a modified version of suzume as a network service, the AGPL requires you to
offer the modified source to its users.

